The taste of the food just remind me of my moms cooking..home cook.. the portion. The taste is all worth the price. But just a tips. Need to come by 11am because..after that timing.. food choices is limited due to high demand.

Just a normal neighbourhood shop. But what makes me keep on coming  to bak ohana is because of the nostalgia taste of home cook food. Whenever i eat here, i just feel like home. And the portion is worth the price. Worth the queue and price. One qord to sum it all up..sooo lazat...
Came at 1pm and no more food. Only a lot of food in packets to be taken away by pre-bookers

Ordered the asam pedas ikan pari and siput sedut. So I've decided to keep this address as my go to for the most delicious asam pedas. The kuah was all rounded flavorful..no regrets. I'm coming back again and again and again. Siput sedut is also a 9,5/10 . Highly recommended üëç
